place.name: INGWORTH
place.gazetteerText: INGWORTH, a parish in Aylsham district, Norfolk: on the river Bure, near the line of ocean telegraph from Norwich to Cromer, 2 miles N of Aylsham and 5¼ W of North Walsham r. station. It has a post office under Norwich. Acres, 512. Real property, £979. Pop., 153. Houses, 37. The property is subdivided. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £127. Patrons, the Trustees of W. H. Wyndham, Esq. The church is ancient, in very good condition; and formerly had a round tower, which fell in 1822. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
